  "local_port": 52070,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is a good inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Fayette County IN?",
  "response": "Finding the right inpatient drug and alcohol rehabilitation center is a crucial step toward recovery. Near Fayette County, Indiana, there are several reputable facilities you might consider. Here's a list of some options, along with key details to help you make an informed decision:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **American Florence - Nashville**\n**Location:** Nashville, IN  \n**Distance from Fayette County:** Approximately 40 miles  \n**Services Offered:**\n- Comprehensive inpatient addiction treatment\n- Medical detoxification\n- Individual and group therapy\n- Relapse prevention programs\n- Aftercare planning  \n**Website:** [American Florence Nashville](https://www.americanflorescence.com/locations/nashville)\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Faithbuilders of Central Indiana**\n**Location:** Indianapolis, IN  \n**Distance from Fayette County:** About 30 miles  \n**Services Offered:**\n- Inpatient treatment for substance use disorders\n- Faith-based recovery programs\n- Counseling and therapy sessions\n- Life skills training  \n**Website:** [Faithbuilders of Central Indiana](https://faithbuilderscindy.org/)\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Midlands Recovery**\n**Location:** Anderson, IN  \n**Distance from Fayette County:** Approximately 15 miles  \n**Services Offered:**\n- Residential addiction treatment\n- Counseling and individual therapy\n- Group therapy sessions\n- Holistic treatment options  \n**Website:** [Midlands Recovery](https://midlandsrecovery.com/)\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Recovery Professionals Group**\n**Location:** Bloomington, IN  \n**Distance from Fayette County:** About 50 miles  \n**Services Offered:**\n- Comprehensive inpatient services\n- Medical detox\n- Behavioral therapy\n- Aftercare support  \n**Website:** [Recovery Professionals Group](https://www.recoveryprofessionalsgroup.com/)\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Southeastern Indiana Treatment Centers**\n**Location:** Various locations across Indiana  \n**Services Offered:**\n- Multiple inpatient facilities\n- Tailored treatment programs\n- Experienced clinical staff  \n**Website:** [Southeastern Indiana Treatment Centers](https://www.sitcco.com/)\n\n---\n\n## **Factors to Consider When Choosing a Rehab Center**\n\n1. **Accreditation and Licensing:** Ensure the facility is accredited by relevant authorities and holds necessary licenses.\n\n2. **Range of Services:** Look for comprehensive programs that include medical detox, therapy (individual and group), holistic treatments, and aftercare planning.\n\n3. **Staff Qualifications:** Qualified and experienced medical and therapeutic staff are essential for effective treatment.\n\n4. **Insurance and Costs:** Verify if the center accepts your insurance or offers flexible payment options.\n\n5. **Location:** Consider proximity to family and support systems, as well as the environment's conduciveness to recovery.\n\n6. **Personal Fit:** It's important that the facility's philosophy and approach align with your personal needs and preferences. Visiting the center can help assess this.\n\n7. **Success Rates and Testimonials:** Research the center\u2019s success stories and read reviews or testimonials from former patients.\n\n---\n\n## **Next Steps**\n\n- **Consult a Healthcare Professional:** Speak with a doctor or addiction specialist to get recommendations tailored to your specific situation.\n\n- **Contact the Centers:** Reach out directly to inquire about their programs, availability, and any questions you might have.\n\n- **Visit if Possible:** Touring the facility can provide valuable insight into whether it's the right fit for you or your loved one.\n\n- **Check with Support Networks:** Organizations like the Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration (SAMHSA) offer resources and assistance in finding treatment centers.  \n  **SAMHSA Helpline:** 1-800-662-HELP (4357)  \n  **Website:** [SAMHSA Treatment Locator](https://findtreatment.samhsa.gov/)\n\n---\n\n**Disclaimer:** While these facilities are known for their services, it's important to conduct personal research and consult with professionals to determine the best fit for your individual needs. Availability, services, and policies may change, so contacting the centers directly is recommended to get the most current information.",
